% ============ COLUMN 1 ============
\begin{column}{\colwidth}

  \begin{block}{The Bloc System}
    Bloc is a bouldering session tracker built as a distributed web service.
    Climbers can log gym sessions and individual climbs from a browser or a
    mobile phone, with all data shared in real time through a single backend.

    \vspace{0.15cm}
    The system was designed to demonstrate a core distributed systems pattern:
    \textbf{multiple independent clients sharing a common server and data store}.
    Neither client holds authoritative state --- both read and write through the
    same REST API, so a session started on the web is immediately visible on
    the mobile app and vice versa.

    \vspace{0.15cm}
    \textbf{Deployed at:} \texttt{dr-aj313798.kemeneth.net}
  \end{block}

  \begin{block}{System Architecture}

    \begin{center}
    \begin{tikzpicture}[
      node distance=1.1cm and 1.6cm,
      box/.style={draw, rounded corners, fill=gray!12, inner sep=8pt,
                  font=\small, text width=3.2cm, align=center},
      sbox/.style={draw, rounded corners, fill=blue!12, inner sep=8pt,
                   font=\small, text width=3.2cm, align=center},
      dbbox/.style={draw, cylinder, shape border rotate=90,
                    fill=orange!15, inner sep=6pt, font=\small, align=center,
                    aspect=0.25},
      arr/.style={-{Latex[length=2.5mm]}, thick},
    ]
      \node[box]  (web)    {Web Browser\\{\footnotesize Handlebars views\\cookie session}};
      \node[box]  (mob)    [below=1.5cm of web] {Mobile App\\{\footnotesize React Native / Expo\\JWT bearer token}};
      \node[sbox] (api)    [right=2.2cm of web, yshift=-0.75cm]
                           {Express Server\\{\footnotesize Node.js\\REST API}};
      \node[dbbox](db)     [right=2.0cm of api] {SQLite\\DB};

      \draw[arr] (web.east) -- node[above,font=\tiny]{HTTP/HTTPS} (api.west |- web.east);
      \draw[arr] (mob.east) -- node[below,font=\tiny]{HTTPS + JWT} (api.west |- mob.east);
      \draw[arr] ([xshift=2pt]api.east) -- node[above,font=\tiny]{SQL} (db.west);
      \draw[arr] (db.west)  -- ([xshift=-2pt]api.east);
    \end{tikzpicture}
    \end{center}

    \vspace{0.1cm}
    The web app uses cookie-based sessions (Express-session) because browsers
    handle cookies natively. The mobile app cannot share that cookie jar, so it
    authenticates with JWTs sent in the \texttt{Authorization: Bearer} header.
    Both paths share the same database rows --- the distribution point is
    purely in the protocol layer, not the data layer.
  \end{block}

  \begin{block}{Technology Stack}
    \begin{center}
    \begin{tabular}{ll}
    \toprule
    \textbf{Layer} & \textbf{Technology} \\
    \midrule
    Mobile client   & React Native, Expo, TypeScript \\
    Web client      & Express, Handlebars, CSS \\
    REST API        & Express (Node.js) \\
    Database        & SQLite3 \\
    Auth (web)      & bcrypt + express-session \\
    Auth (mobile)   & bcrypt + JWT (jsonwebtoken) \\
    File uploads    & Multer (5\,MB limit, image validation) \\
    Hosting         & VPS at \texttt{kemeneth.net} \\
    \bottomrule
    \end{tabular}
    \end{center}
  \end{block}

  \begin{block}{References}
    \footnotesize
    \begin{itemize}\setlength\itemsep{0pt}
